<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>Wide Area Persistent Surveillance using Wide Area <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Motion</del> <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Imagery</del> is capable of live viewing and recording a 68 square mile area with enough detail to view pedestrians and vehicles.&lt;ref&gt;https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.216676585110830.39548.100003054700769&amp;type=3 {{Dead link|date=September 2013}}&lt;/ref&gt; These gigapixel cameras, such as Gorgon Stare, Angelfire, Hawkeye and ARGUS,&lt;ref&gt;{{Wayback |date=20100131011638 |url=http://www.darpa.mil/ipto/programs/argus/argus.asp |title="Autonomous Real-time Ground Ubiquitous Surveillance - Imaging System (ARGUS-IS)" }}, Information Processing Processing Techniques Office, U.S. Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA). Retrieved 19 September 2013.&lt;/ref&gt; create airborne video so detailed that pedestrians can be followed across the city through forensic analysis. This allows investigators to rewind and playback the movements of anyone within this 68 square mile area.</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">+</td>
  <td class="diff-addedline"><div>Wide Area Persistent Surveillance using <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">[[</ins>Wide Area <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Persistent</ins> <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Surveillance Systems|WAMI]]</ins> is capable of live viewing and recording a 68 square mile area with enough detail to view pedestrians and vehicles.&lt;ref&gt;https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.216676585110830.39548.100003054700769&amp;type=3 {{Dead link|date=September 2013}}&lt;/ref&gt; These gigapixel cameras, such as Gorgon Stare, Angelfire, Hawkeye and ARGUS,&lt;ref&gt;{{Wayback |date=20100131011638 |url=http://www.darpa.mil/ipto/programs/argus/argus.asp |title="Autonomous Real-time Ground Ubiquitous Surveillance - Imaging System (ARGUS-IS)" }}, Information Processing Processing Techniques Office, U.S. Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA). Retrieved 19 September 2013.&lt;/ref&gt; create airborne video so detailed that pedestrians can be followed across the city through forensic analysis. This allows investigators to rewind and playback the movements of anyone within this 68 square mile area.</div></td>
</tr>
